    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Black-figure kylikes of type A, generally of the 6th century BCE, decorated on the outside with a pair of large eyes on each side, often with figures painted between the eyes and sometimes under the handles as well. On some rare eye cups, moldmade male genitals substitue for the wheelmade foot.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046899/Clark, Elston and Hart, Understanding Greek Vases (2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zwartfigurige kylikes van het type A, over het algemeen uit de 6de eeuw v. Chr., aan de buitenkant versierd met een paar grote ogen aan beide zijden, vaak met figuren tussen de ogen en soms ook onder de handvatten geschilderd. Bij sommige zeldzame ogenschalen nemen geperste mannelijke geslachtsdelen de plaats in van de gedraaide voet.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>黑繪式A型雙耳盞，一般製於西元前6世紀，在杯面兩側有一對眼睛作裝飾，通常在雙眼的中間或把手之下繪有其他圖形。有些罕見的眼睛杯會用鑄模製的男性生殖器取代其陶輪製的底足。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tipo A kylikes a figure nere, generalmente del VI secolo a.C., decorate esternamente con un paio di grandi occhi su lati, spesso con figure dipinte tra gli occhi e talvolta sotto le maniglie. In alcune rare coppe ad occhioni, i genitali maschili sostituiscono il piede.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Italian</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109543/Italian Term Processing (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Schwarzfigurige Kylix der Form A, üblicherweise aus dem 6. Jh. v. Chr., auf der Außenseite bemalt mit einem Paar großer Augen auf jeder Seite. Häufig mit Figuren zwischen den Augen und auch unter den Henkeln. Einige seltene Augenschalen besitzen modelgefertigte männliche Genitalien als Fuß anstatt des scheibengedrehten Fußes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
